  "prompt": "How much refund will I get on my PRS counter ticket if my seat is waitlisted even after the departure of the train? Can I board the train using it",
  "response": "If your seat is waitlisted even after the departure of the train, you are generally entitled to a full refund of the fare paid for the PRS (Passenger Reservation System) counter ticket. As per Indian Railways rules, if your waitlisted ticket does not get confirmed or moved to RAC (Reservation Against Cancellation) status, you cannot board the train. You should ideally cancel your waitlisted ticket to obtain the refund.\n\nThe refund process for a waitlisted PRS counter ticket typically involves canceling the ticket at the counter before the departure of the train or within a stipulated time frame post-departure, usually up to 30 minutes after the train's departure. Always check the latest guidelines from Indian Railways or their official website for the most accurate and updated information regarding refunds and cancellations.",
